    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-09-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="648"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                <head>No. 648.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">de Muruaga</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Spanish Legation in Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,<lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-09-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 1, 1887</date>. (Received September
                        2.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The undersigned, envoy extraordinary and minister plenipotentiary of Her Majesty
                    the Queen Regent of Spain, has the honor to return to the Hon. T. F. Bayard,
                    Secretary of State, as requested in his note of yesterday, the annexed
                        memorandum<note n="*" xml:id="d648fn1">Published, <ref target="#pg_1034">p.
                            1034</ref>, <hi rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                    </note> regulating the commercial relations between Spain and the United
                    States.</p>
                <p>The undersigned finds the text of the said document perfectly correct, and in
                    harmony with the declarations made in the late notes exchanged for that purpose
                    between Her Majesty’s legation and the Department of State, and he leaves to the
                    honorable Mr. Bayard’s decision the naming the day and hour agreeable to him for
                    proceeding to the signing and sealing of the same.</p>
                <p>The undersigned, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. de Muruaga.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
